    {
      "bookmarkId": "3300054384_3_554-646",
      "chapterUid": 3,
      "range": "554-646",
      "markText": "想要将某个人归入某一类别（朋友或敌人；值得信任或不值得信任）是人类与生俱来的天性，这种渴求为智力发展提供了基础。如果我们不去构成类别，我们就只能注意到个例，而触及不到任何总体性的思考。",
      "totalCount": 253,
      "appLink": "weread://bestbookmark?bookId=3300054384&chapterUid=3&rangeStart=554&rangeEnd=646",
      "webLink": "https://weread.qq.com/web/reader/44132240813ab7bbeg01417c?chapterUid=3&rangeStart=554&rangeEnd=646"
    },
    {
      "bookmarkId": "3300054384_3_2637-2721",
      "chapterUid": 3,
      "range": "2637-2721",
      "markText": "认知心理学和机器学习之间存在着另一个深刻的区别。心理学主要是描述性的，它回答人们实际上是如何进行分类的问题，而机器学习是规范性的，它回答的是人们应该如何进行分类的问题。",
      "totalCount": 112,
      "appLink": "weread://bestbookmark?bookId=3300054384&chapterUid=3&rangeStart=2637&rangeEnd=2721",
      "webLink": "https://weread.qq.com/web/reader/44132240813ab7bbeg01417c?chapterUid=3&rangeStart=2637&rangeEnd=2721"
    },
    {
      "bookmarkId": "3300054384_3_1440-1457",
      "chapterUid": 3,
      "range": "1440-1457",
      "markText": "人们无法提前知道所有可能发生的事件",
      "totalCount": 108,
      "appLink": "weread://bestbookmark?bookId=3300054384&chapterUid=3&rangeStart=1440&rangeEnd=1457",
      "webLink": "https://weread.qq.com/web/reader/44132240813ab7bbeg01417c?chapterUid=3&rangeStart=1440&rangeEnd=1457"
    },
    {
      "bookmarkId": "3300054384_4_2591-2606",
      "chapterUid": 4,
      "range": "2591-2606",
      "markText": "现实情境中，简单规则表现良好。",
      "totalCount": 98,
      "appLink": "weread://bestbookmark?bookId=3300054384&chapterUid=4&rangeStart=2591&rangeEnd=2606",
      "webLink": "https://weread.qq.com/web/reader/44132240813ab7bbeg01417c?chapterUid=4&rangeStart=2591&rangeEnd=2606"
    },
    {
      "bookmarkId": "3300054384_3_2472-2514",
      "chapterUid": 3,
      "range": "2472-2514",
      "markText": "本书致力于提高不确定性环境中的透明度，为读者提供了易于理解、记忆、教授和执行的工具。",
      "totalCount": 90,
      "appLink": "weread://bestbookmark?bookId=3300054384&chapterUid=3&rangeStart=2472&rangeEnd=2514",
      "webLink": "https://weread.qq.com/web/reader/44132240813ab7bbeg01417c?chapterUid=3&rangeStart=2472&rangeEnd=2514"
    },
    {
      "bookmarkId": "3300054384_4_812-971",
      "chapterUid": 4,
      "range": "812-971",
      "markText": "分类有两个常见的含义：其一是，确定一组类别的行为，即建立分类系统；其二是，确定分类规则并将每个对象分配给某一给定类别的行为。在这本书中，我们探讨的是第二个含义。这些分类可以为两个目标服务：诊断和预测。",
      "totalCount": 90,
      "appLink": "weread://bestbookmark?bookId=3300054384&chapterUid=4&rangeStart=812&rangeEnd=971",
      "webLink": "https://weread.qq.com/web/reader/44132240813ab7bbeg01417c?chapterUid=4&rangeStart=812&rangeEnd=971"
    },
    {
      "bookmarkId": "3300054384_4_729-754",
      "chapterUid": 4,
      "range": "729-754",
      "markText": "分类是指根据线索使用分类规则将个体分配到各个类别。",
      "totalCount": 88,
      "appLink": "weread://bestbookmark?bookId=3300054384&chapterUid=4&rangeStart=729&rangeEnd=754",
      "webLink": "https://weread.qq.com/web/reader/44132240813ab7bbeg01417c?chapterUid=4&rangeStart=729&rangeEnd=754"
    },
    {
      "bookmarkId": "3300054384_3_2570-2608",
      "chapterUid": 3,
      "range": "2570-2608",
      "markText": "本书还认为机器学习应首先构建透明的算法，而不是事后再去试图解释不透明的算法。",
      "totalCount": 85,
      "appLink": "weread://bestbookmark?bookId=3300054384&chapterUid=3&rangeStart=2570&rangeEnd=2608",
      "webLink": "https://weread.qq.com/web/reader/44132240813ab7bbeg01417c?chapterUid=3&rangeStart=2570&rangeEnd=2608"
    },
    {
      "bookmarkId": "3300054384_4_2035-2072",
      "chapterUid": 4,
      "range": "2035-2072",
      "markText": "在现实情境中，未来可能以不可预知的方式不同于过去，最佳分类规则是不可知的。",
